article:
This is a 'list of the municipalities of Portugal'. Portugal is divided into
18 districts () and 2 autonomous regions (), Azores and Madeira. The districts
and autonomous regions are further sub-divided into 308 '[[municipalities of
Portugal]]' ( or ). Usually, a municipality has the name of its biggest town
or city, or at least, of its historically most important town or city,
however, the municipality is, usually, much larger than the city or town after
which it is named.
